			<h2>Goethe’s Faust. A Genetic Edition</h2>

			<p>Goethe’ s Faust is the centrepiece of German literature and a landmark of world literature. 
			The project of a genetic edition of Goethe’s masterwork intends to make all extant manuscripts 
			accessible and to reconstruct the genetic relations between them. Complete transcriptions will 
			help deciphering the facsimilies and the development of proper visualisation strategies will  
			give a model of how scholarly editions for the 21st century may look like. At the same time it 
			aims at making the texts of Faust open to any reading interest the general reader might have.</p>

			<p>The project is headed by Professor Anne Bohnenkamp-Renken 
			(<a href="http://www.goethehaus-frankfurt.de/" title="Homepage">Freies Deutsches Hochstift</a>), Dr Silke Henke
			(<a href="http://www.klassik-stiftung.de/einrichtungen/goethe-und-schiller-archiv.html" title="Homepage">Goethe- und
			Schiller-Archiv</a>) and Professor Fotis Jannidis
			(<a href="http://www.digital-humanities.de/" title="Homepage">Julius-Maximilians-Universität Würzburg</a>). 
			It is funded by the <a href="http://www.dfg.de/" title="Homepage">Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft</a>
			(German Research Foundation).</p>	

